{"type":null,"faqId":38033,"title":"How can I reduce mobile data usage","answer":"<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\r\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\r\n.s1{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\r\n.s2{font-weight:bold;}\r\n.p1{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\r\n.p2{margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\r\n</style>\n<div>\n<p><span>Connect to a Wi-Fi network if there is one available.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Turn off the mobile data connection when you are not using mobile data.</span> </p>\n<p><span>When browsing web pages, you can prevent images from loading on the page if you do not need to view them.</span> </p>\n<p><span>In the </span><span class=\"s2\">Browser</span><span> interface, open the options menu, select </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings &gt; Bandwidth management</span><span> and deselect </span><span class=\"s2\">Load images</span><span>.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Disable background data syncing if not needed.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Swipe downwards from the status bar to display shortcut switches and then touch </span><img style=\"WIDTH: 0.305in; HEIGHT: 0.223in; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-bottom\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=123150\"><span> to turn off the auto sync function.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Close the apps that you are not using.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Open the list of recently-used apps and close the apps that you are no longer using.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Stop apps in the background from accessing the Internet via mobile data.</span> </p>\n<p><span>Go to </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings</span><span> and select </span><span class=\"s2\">Networked apps</span><span>. Then select the apps for which you want to restrict Internet access and turn off the corresponding mobile data switch.</span> </p>\n</div>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":281,"languageName":"fa","faqCode":"3253","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1441091742000,"seriesProductName":"ALE-L21,CherryPlus-L11,CHM-U01,EDGE-U00,G510-0010,G510-0200,G525-U00,G610-U00,G610-U20,G615-U10,G630-U10,G630-U20,G6-U10,G700-U10,G730-U10,G750-U10,G760-L01,GRA-L03,H30-U10,H60-L04,Holly-U19,Jazz-L09,Jazz-L11,MT1-U06,PLK-L01,RIO-L01,Sophia-L10,U8950-1,U9508,Y210-0200,Y220-U10,Y221-U22,Y300-0000,Y330-U01,Y330-U11,Y336-U02,Y360-U61,Y511-U30,Y520-U22,Y530-U00,Y550-L01,Y560-U02,Y600-U20,Y625-U32,Y635-L21","visitedTimes":14,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"mobile data usage; data usage","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}